504→   504→use anyhow;
505→   505→
506→   506→/// Permission mode controls what tools are available and how iteration approval works.
507→   507→///
508→   508→/// | Mode       | When to use              | Gate behavior                           |
509→   509→/// |------------|--------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
510→   510→/// | `Readonly` | Auditing / inspection    | Restricts toolset to read-only tools    |
511→   511→/// | `Standard` | Normal development       | Threshold-based auto-approve (<=N files)|
512→   512→/// | `Autonomous`| Well-tested, CI         | Auto-approves all iterations            |
513→   513→/// | `Strict`   | Sensitive / high-risk    | Requires manual approval every iteration|
514→   514→///
